<br>
I've been playing EQ about 2 1/2 years now, and haven't played ANY other computer games since I started. It's absorbed countless hours of my life and I don't regret a minute of it... yet. It's brought me a lot of fun and satisfaction, and many new friends.<br>
<br>
10 (ish) server clusters of 5/6 servers, 3 Continents, 9.95 a month.<br>
30 (ish) server clusters of 12/15 servers, 6 Continents (7 including PoP), 12.95 a month.<br>
<br>
Unreasonable?<br>
<br>
My biggest concern with the increased competition is for the longevity of EQ. I love this game, I've put many hours work into my characters and learning what has become a new state of exsistence, and I want to carry on for the foreseable future. I want to be done with EQ long before EQ is done with me.<br>
<br>
I'd rather they put up the price to 15.00 or 20.00, make pots of cash, and invest it back into the game, than turn around in 12 months time and say it's not &quot;economically viable&quot; to continue.<br>
<br>
I've seen people argue that we've already paid for the increased content by buying all the expansion packs. But lets open our eyes here. You already accept from day one that by paying 9.95/month the cost of the box in the store is insignificant and it's the subscription that pays for your entertainment. <br>
<br>
With the increased cost in power, band-width, server maintenance and staffing I'm amazed it's taken this long to put up the price and I'm surprised the increase is so little. I fully expected a price increase with the release of Velious.<br>
<br>
So my question to Verant/Sony, is 2.95 enough?<br>
